{"page":1,"prev_page_endpoint":null,"next_page_endpoint":null,"total_pages":1,"reasons":[{"created_at":"2014-05-13T15:41:40Z","content":"I want to encourage people to go to college and be able to afford to live  after graduation.  I think the  interest rate should be less than 4%.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Josephine McClure","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/94094772"},{"created_at":"2014-05-13T15:34:27Z","content":"Have 3 college kids","like_count":1,"author_name":"Nancy Davis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/94092748"},{"created_at":"2014-05-13T16:23:36Z","content":"I'd rather see the cost of higher education be lowered. but that doesn't help any existing debts.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Chad Wagner","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9087762"},{"created_at":"2014-05-13T18:40:48Z","content":"Student load debt is destroying the financial future of our country.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Robert White","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/94164536"},{"created_at":"2014-05-16T05:11:04Z","content":"Education should not be the franchise that it is. We should not cripple people who get an education so that others are discouraged from even trying from the very fear of crushing debt for the rest of their lives. I am not the only one who decided not to marry my significant other because we didn't want to share our student debt. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ruth White","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/73163082"},{"created_at":"2014-05-14T00:39:20Z","content":"I paid on my student loan for ten years.  My child is still paying on a loan.  I'm for anything that might help keep down the cost of higher education.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Richard McClure","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/94274720"},{"created_at":"2014-05-17T03:33:26Z","content":"I've had loans in deferment for years and can't catch up.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Charles Sebastian II","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/95889040"},{"created_at":"2014-05-15T17:47:55Z","content":"My children have student loans which they are trying to repay.  The current interest rates are too high for students.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Robert Keynton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/95120675"},{"created_at":"2014-05-13T21:55:58Z","content":"I have two grown children who are barely living paycheck to paycheck.  Their student loan payments are more than their mortgage or rent.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lisa White","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/57002140"},{"created_at":"2014-05-22T23:56:42Z","content":"Starting out with debt can stop you from attaining your dream & what you went to college for. If you can't find work in your chosen field you settle for a job to pay for this debt and can get locked into the cycle of \"some day\" when I get this paid I can have the life I want.  Usually not, unless you're very lucky.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christine Kramlich","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/99468120"}]}